\begin_layout Standard
Chromosomal translocations are frequently observed within cancer cells and
 can be one of the initiating events leading to oncogenesis.
 Leukaemias are one of the best studied cancer models due to the ease of
 accessibility of the affected cells; many of the best characterised cancer
 pathologies have been within leukaemias.
 
\end_layout

