\begin_layout Subsubsection
Mechanisms of 
\emph on
MLL
\emph default
 translocation formation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A clue to how translocations form within the 
\emph on
MLL 
\emph default
gene comes from the observation that 11q23 translocations are especially
 prevalent in therapy-related leukaemias - secondary leukaemias that develop
 in patients after treatment for a primary cancer with topoisomerase II
 inhibitors 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Krivtsov2007"

\end_inset

.
 Topoisomerases are found in all eukaryotic nuclei and are able to relieve
 supercoiling and promote chromosome disentanglement 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Buck2004"

\end_inset

.
 They function by binding DNA, forming a transient double strand break and
 passing another strand of DNA through the gap, before ligating the DSB.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Topoisomerases are important in transcription, which creates supercoils
 as template DNA is processed through static RNA polymerase II enzymes 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Liu1987"

\end_inset

.
 DNA topoisomerase II associates with gene promoters 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Collins2001"

\end_inset

 and is required for the transcription of genes longer than 3 Kbp in yeast
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Joshi2012"

\end_inset

.
 Topoisomerase II induced DSBs have been implicated in the regulation of
 certain genes via the assembly of transcription complexes and changes in
 chromatin structure 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Ju2006"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
DNA topoisomerase II inhibitors are commonly used as chemotherapeutic agents
 and work by decreasing the ligation rate, disrupting the cleavage / ligation
 equilibrium.
 This leads to an increase in DNA cleavage and an accumulation of DSBs,
 triggering the cell DNA damage response and leading to cell death by apoptosis
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Burden1998"

\end_inset

.
 Topoisomerase II inhibitors are widely used chemotherapeutic agents, effective
 against a range of malignancies including small-cell lung cancer and gonadal
 tumours 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Arnold1981"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

