e digestion, with a greater degree of local diffusion seen in the absence
 of the Ku80 DNA-end binding protein 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Soutoglou2007"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The contact first model of translocation formation has large implications
 within the field of nuclear organisation, as it requires specific chromosomal
 contacts within cells prior to translocation.
\end_layout

